ðŸš€ 1. Auto-Post to Instagram (Official Instagram Graph API)
âœ” Requirements

Meta Developer Account

Instagram Business Account

Facebook Page linked to Instagram

Permanent Access Token

Instagram Business Account ID

âœ” Supports:

Posting images + caption

Posting videos + caption

ðŸ“Œ Python Code: Post Image + Caption to Instagram

Install:

pip install requests python-dotenv


Create instagram_poster.py:

import requests
import os
from dotenv import load_dotenv

load_dotenv()

ACCESS_TOKEN = os.getenv("IG_ACCESS_TOKEN")
IG_USER_ID = os.getenv("IG_USER_ID")   # Instagram Business Account ID


def post_to_instagram(image_url, caption):
    # Step 1: Create media container
    create_url = (
        f"https://graph.facebook.com/v18.0/{IG_USER_ID}/media"
        f"?image_url={image_url}"
        f"&caption={caption}"
        f"&access_token={ACCESS_TOKEN}"
    )

    create_res = requests.post(create_url).json()

    if "id" not in create_res:
        return create_res
    
    container_id = create_res["id"]

    # Step 2: Publish container
    publish_url = (
        f"https://graph.facebook.com/v18.0/{IG_USER_ID}/media_publish"
        f"?creation_id={container_id}"
        f"&access_token={ACCESS_TOKEN}"
    )

    publish_res = requests.post(publish_url).json()
    return publish_res


if __name__ == "__main__":
    img = "https://example.com/my_image.jpg"
    caption = """Your Instagram Caption Here"""

    result = post_to_instagram(img, caption)
    print(result)

ðŸš€ 2. Auto-Post to YouTube (YouTube Data API)
âœ” Requirements

Google Cloud Project

OAuth Client ID

YouTube Data API enabled

client_secret.json file

Install:

pip install google-auth-oauthlib google-api-python-client python-dotenv

ðŸ“Œ Python Code: Upload a Video to YouTube

Create youtube_uploader.py:

import os
from googleapiclient.discovery import build
from googleapiclient.http import MediaFileUpload
from google_auth_oauthlib.flow import InstalledAppFlow

SCOPES = ["https://www.googleapis.com/auth/youtube.upload"]

def youtube_auth():
    flow = InstalledAppFlow.from_client_secrets_file(
        "client_secret.json", SCOPES
    )
    creds = flow.run_local_server(port=0)
    return creds


def upload_video(file_path, title, description):
    creds = youtube_auth()
    youtube = build("youtube", "v3", credentials=creds)

    request_body = {
        "snippet": {
            "title": title,
            "description": description,
            "categoryId": "22"
        },
        "status": {
            "privacyStatus": "public"
        }
    }

    media = MediaFileUpload(file_path, chunksize=-1, resumable=True)

    request = youtube.videos().insert(
        part="snippet,status",
        body=request_body,
        media_body=media
    )

    response = request.execute()
    return response


if __name__ == "__main__":
    result = upload_video(
        file_path="video.mp4",
        title="My AI-Generated Video",
        description="This video was posted automatically using Python!"
    )
    print(result)

ðŸš€ 3. Combine Both Into the AI Workflow Automation

After the AI generates:

Blog

Social posts

YouTube title

YouTube description

You can auto-post like this:

from instagram_poster import post_to_instagram
from youtube_uploader import upload_video

# FROM AI WORKFLOW RESULT
caption = result["social_posts"]
youtube_title = result["youtube"]["title"]
youtube_desc = result["youtube"]["description"]

# Instagram
post_to_instagram(
    image_url="https://your-ai-generated-image.com/image.jpg",
    caption=caption
)

# YouTube
upload_video(
    file_path="generated_video.mp4",
    title=youtube_title,
    description=youtube_desc
)

